I find you get the most mileage out of drawing from life at first, personally speaking. Get a lamp, a few objects and rearrange them with lighting. Then, do your best to imitate what you see. Ideally, you’d do this on decent sized paper, traditionally, using a technique like this to help. https://drawingacademy.com/how-to-measure-with-a-pencil

It feels harder in some ways, but like a complex exercise it works out so many art muscles at once you will improve at a crazy level. I won’t say it’s the easiest, but each piece has direction and an easy goal: draw what you see. But that’s just my two cents, I’m no expert.
